title: Dialogflow - Create a prebuilt agent
abstract:
# Dialogflow - Create a prebuilt agent
The first step in this tutorial is to create an agent. Rather than building an agent from scratch, you will import a telecommunications [prebuilt agent](/dialogflow/cx/docs/concept/agents-prebuilt) . Using a prebuilt agent will accelerate your progress for this tutorial.
To import a prebuilt agent to your project:
- Go to the [Dialogflow CX Console](https://dialogflow.cloud.google.com/cx/projects) .
- Select the project where you would like to import the prebuilt agent or click **Create Project** to create a new project.
- Click **Use pre-built agents** .
- Click the **Telecommunications** prebuilt agent.
- Click **Import as agent** .
- A dialog box opens.
- Choose your desired [location](/dialogflow/cx/docs/concept/region#avail) .
- Click **Create** .In the next step, you will create a webhook service required for this agent
